@w05

; 回想
@bg f=0027
[texton w=2]
As a snowstorm raged, I clung to my mother as she lay in bed in a small, remote cabin.[k]
It was very cold inside the hut. Even though I was trying to keep warm, I wasn't getting any warmer.[k]

I desperately called out to her, sobbing, over and over again. Please don't die.[k]
But she didn't answer.[k]
A doctor and several adults were there, but they all looked resigned.[k]
Everyone just stood there looking down at my mother without any emotion. I was the only one who was desperate.[k]
Soon I couldn't hear her breathing. I called out to her even more frantically.[k]
However, my mother's warm body, gradually began to get colder.[k]
Eventually, when I realized my mother would never come back, my emotions died too.[k]
All that was there was the noise of the blizzard outside and the freezing air...[k]
[textoff]
@out
@w1

